* {{cite journal |last1= Ottonia |first1= Federica |last2= Blasi |first2= Carlo |title= Results of a 60-Year Monitoring System for Santa Maria del Fiore Dome in Florence |journal= International Journal of Architectural Heritage: Conservation, Analysis, and Restoration |volume= 9 |issue= 1 |pages= 7–24 |publisher=  Taylor & Francis |year= 2015  |url= https://www.researchgate.net/publication/271756310}}
* Ricci, Massimo, [http://www.sillabe.it/it/home/447-il-genio-di-filippo-brunelleschi-.html ''Il genio di Brunelleschi e la costruzione della Cupola di Santa Maria del Fiore''], Livorno : Casa Editrice Sillabe S.r.l., April 2014. (''The genius of Filippo Brunelleschi and the construction of the dome of Santa Maria del Fiore''). {{ISBN|978-88-8347-691-4}}. The book is the result of forty years of research on the secret technique with which Brunelleschi built the Dome of Santa Maria del Fiore in Florence. Ricci makes the case for the dome being an [[inverted_arch|inverted arch]] and uses a [[herringbone_pattern|herringbone pattern]] (''spina a pesce'') for the dome's bricks.
* Vereycken, Karel, [http://schillerinstitute.org/educ/pedagogy/2013/vereycken-dome-1.html "The Secrets of the Florentine Dome"], ''[[Schiller_Institute|Schiller Institute]]'', 2013. (Translation from the French, [http://www.solidariteetprogres.org/documents-de-fond-7/culture/les-secrets-du-dome-de-florence "Les secrets du dôme de Florence"], la revue ''Fusion'', n° 96, Mai, Juin 2003)
{{refend}}

